<br>
example Plane of storms group six 61+ mages using 61 air pet<br>
hasted burnout IV-V<br>
<br>
the damage mitigation from the stuns is very noticable some fights no pets would die.<br>
<br>
if a pet would die summon a new one<br>
<br>
if the mob enrages everyone nukes @ 10% health = bypass enrage, also people backed off pet out of habit heh. /pet hold would also work<br>
<br>
with this combo we could kill 2 at once in Plane of storms easily to deal with adds<br>
<br>
2 deaths in 6 hours both avoidable deaths too not due to team weakness. ( i would challange you to charm PoP stuff for 6 straight hours and not die once or twice that seems highly unlikey due to nature of charm breaking at wrong moment )<br>
<br>
we held a giant camp and killed yard trash between spawns<br>
<br>
awsome group i would do again, calling us disorganized is crap, we where highly organized 1 person pulled or issued command to rush ( usually cause casters couldn't be pulled easily ) puller never died. <br>
<br>
exp was very group comparable or better to normal exp group<br>
<br>
conclusion: all pet group can and will work despite magesthink posts to the contrary. enchanter charming is highly dangerous more dangerous than an all mage group because your putting all your strength in 1 pet and 1 character. any group that would let more than 1 enchanter charm would be put to very high risk. i would have more faith in an all ranger group snare/root bowing things to death than a all enchanter group after a while your luck will run out and you will wipe. now that being said yes charmed mobs are powerful but also highly dangerous. how hectic would it be to even have 2 enchanters charming mobs to kill stuff. <br>
<br>
bottom line <br>
6 mages with six 61+ mage pets + nukes will always outdamage be faster and safer than 1 enchanter with 1 charmed mob. and you cant have more than 1 enchanter with charmed mobs you luck will run out eventually<br>
